benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/admin/queues - Get queues entries

covered: Valid Request: Happy paths with default behavior and filtering are well covered (TC01–TC10, TC23), including verification of application/octet-stream content type (TC01).
Empty Response: Covered for no data in the system and filters matching nothing (TC11, TC29).

Query Parameters: Broad coverage of valid and invalid inputs, including accountId/queueName/serviceName, date range, and feature flags toggled to false; combinations also tested (TC02–TC10, TC23, TC24, TC25).
Error Scenarios: 400 for invalid accountId and malformed date; 404 for account not found; unexpected param tolerance (TC12, TC13, TC14, TC25).
Resilience/Failures: 500/503/504 and transient network recovery tested (TC16, TC19, TC27, TC30).
Security/Injection: SQLi and XSS attempts covered with safe handling expectations (TC17, TC26).
Performance: Large data volume retrieval with response time check (TC18).
Backward compatibility/regression: Defaults and prior bug regression validated (TC21, TC22).
gaps: Pagination: No scenarios verify pagination behavior for large datasets (page/size/next links). If not supported by this endpoint, this should be explicitly clarified.
Rate Limiting: No tests for throttling/429 responses and Retry-After headers under burst load.
Caching Behavior: No verification of caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control, Last-Modified) or conditional requests (If-None-Match/If-Modified-Since).
Octet-stream payload validation: Only content type is asserted; there is no validation that the binary decodes/parses into the expected queue entries structure and fields.

Content-type consistency: Success content type is only verified once (TC01). Other success paths do not assert application/octet-stream; error responses do not consistently assert JSON error schema beyond TC28.
Date parameter edge cases: No tests for providing only minDate or only maxDate; invalid range (minDate > maxDate); timezone/ISO-8601 normalization.
Boolean parameter validation: No tests for explicit true values, case variations (True/TRUE), or invalid booleans (e.g., withHistory=maybe) leading to 400.
Authorization depth: 403 Forbidden not covered for authenticated but unauthorized principals (non-admin).
Input encoding/characters: No tests for URL-encoded names, whitespace, or very long values for queueName/serviceName (length/character set constraints).
recommendations: Add pagination scenarios: large dataset with page/size parameters, navigation (next/prev), and stable ordering; if the API does not support pagination, document as not applicable.
Introduce rate limiting tests: burst requests leading to 429 with Retry-After; verify headers and backoff behavior.
Add caching tests: assert ETag/Cache-Control/Last-Modified on 200; exercise conditional GETs (If-None-Match/If-Modified-Since) expecting 304.

Validate octet-stream payload content: define and assert the serialized format (e.g., CSV/JSON-in-archive), field presence, and correctness after decoding; include Content-Disposition filename if applicable.
Assert content types consistently: for all successful filter combinations verify application/octet-stream; for error paths assert JSON error schema and Content-Type=application/json.
Expand date tests: only minDate, only maxDate, minDate > maxDate -> 400, timezone handling, and strict ISO-8601 formats.
Expand boolean validation: tests for withHistory=true explicitly, case-insensitive values, and invalid boolean inputs returning 400.
Add 403 scenario: authenticated non-admin or insufficient permissions should receive 403 Forbidden.
Add input encoding tests: URL-encoded values, leading/trailing spaces, and maximum length constraints for queueName/serviceName with expected outcomes.
